  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6587 sitting below the massive 6600 gamma wall (66.7B) in a PIN regime, dealers are likely buying the dip here as they're positioned long gamma, creating natural support around current levels with additional buying pressure if we test the 6570 negative gamma zone. The towering positive gamma walls from 6590-6610 form a strong magnetic pull that should compress price action and drive mean reversion toward the 6600 flip strike, especially given the massive GEX surge we just detected. \n\nWatch 6600 as the critical inflection point - any sustained break above triggers dealer selling pressure, while a move toward 6570 accelerates dealer buying into negative gamma territory.",
